description: President Gustavo Petro met with Colombia’s central bank board a day after accusing them of throttling the nation’s economic growth.
title: Petro Meets Colombian Central Bankers He Blamed for Weak Economy

description: The East African country is host to Chinese, French and US naval bases — but it has warned Washington not to use its territory to confront Houthi militants attacking global trade.
title: ‘Don’t Bring the War Here’: How Tiny Djibouti Navigated Red Sea Crisis

description: Chancellor of the Exchequer Jeremy Hunt will pledge to reduce UK taxes after a looming UK general election if his governing Conservatives come out on top, in a speech Friday in which he’ll also reiterate an ambition to eliminate the country’s national insurance payroll tax.
title: Hunt Vows Conservatives Will Cut Taxes If They Win UK Election

description: This is Washington Edition, the newsletter about money, power and politics in the nation’s capital. Today, senior Washington correspondent Saleha Mohsin and producer Julia Press look for the Big Take DC podcast at how the Trump campaign operation has changed. Sign up here and follow us at @bpolitics. Email our editors here.
title: Trump Finds Third Time’s a Charm for Running a Campaign

description: Donald Trump’s lawyer at his hush money trial grilled Michael Cohen for hours on the witness stand Thursday about possible inconsistencies in his testimony and his well-documented history of lying under oath.
title: Trump Defense Gets Boost From Tough Cohen Cross-Examination

description: The US government is open to easing sanctions on billionaire mining magnate Dan Gertler if he gives up his business operations and assets in the Democratic Republic of Congo, where Washington’s interest in critical minerals has run up against his problematic royalties ownership.
title: Biden Open to Easing Sanctions on Billionaire Gertler in Return for Congo Exit

description: The Brazilian government is weighing additional measures to help combat the fallout from historic floods in the state of Rio Grande do Sul, just days after unveiling a 52 billion reais ($10 billion) aid plan.
title: Brazil Eyes Further Aid After $10 Billion Plan to Combat Floods

description: Far-right lawmaker Geert Wilders pulled off a surprise victory in a Dutch election in November, after a late surge catapulted his anti-European Union party past its rivals. On May 15, after months of negotiations, he sealed a tentative agreement to form a right-wing coalition government with three other parties. Wilders was forced to renounce his own bid to become premier as part of the deal. But as leader of the largest bloc in parliament, he will still make key decisions behind the scenes.
title: Who Is Geert Wilders, the Far-Right Kingmaker of the Next Dutch Government?

description: The Justice Department formally started the procedure of classifying marijuana as a less dangerous substance, moving toward a major change in US drug policy.
title: DOJ Advances Plan to Classify Marijuana as Less Dangerous Drug

description: A congressional committee hammered Harvard University for “major flaws” in its response to antisemitism on campus following Hamas’s Oct. 7 attack on Israel, saying the school’s failures led to a hostile environment for Jewish students.
title: Harvard Slammed in House Probe for ‘Inaction’ on Antisemitism

description: Chad’s top court rejected an opposition appeal to cancel the May 6 presidential election and declared the country’s military ruler the winner.
title: Chad’s Top Court Upholds Election Result in Blow to Opposition

description: Canada has the workers it needs to build 70% more homes a year and municipal red tape is the main barrier to construction, according to the nation’s housing agency.
title: Trudeau Housing Push Challenged by Weak Productivity, Study Says

description: The International Monetary Fund criticized the Biden administration’s decision this week to aggressively raise tariffs on some Chinese goods, underscoring its warning that tensions between the world’s top two economies risk hurting global trade and growth.
title: US ‘Better Served’ With Open Trade Than China Tariffs, IMF Says

description: The US has finished building a floating pier that will help bring more aid to the Gaza Strip, the Pentagon said, even as officials acknowledged the new structure won’t fill the gap in need created by the war between Hamas and Israel.
title: Pentagon Finishes Pier That Will Bring Fresh Aid to Gaza Strip

description: Vice President Kamala Harris is willing to debate Republican Donald Trump’s choice for running mate on either July 23 or Aug. 13, President Joe Biden’s campaign said.
title: Harris Offers Debate Dates for Showdown With Trump Running Mate

description: Kosovo’s government offered a concession on the key issue of autonomy for its ethnic Serb minority as the Balkan nation seeks to put its bid to join the Council of Europe back on track.
title: Kosovo Offers Concession on Serb Autonomy in Bid for Recognition

description: This year’s resurgence in cryptocurrency markets has made digital assets a hot topic on the campaign trail before US elections in November, and the political battle lines are becoming much more well-defined.
title: Trump Mugshot NFTs Highlight Crypto’s Arrival on Campaign Trail

description: Chile’s government decided to fast track its pension reform as President Gabriel Boric pressures lawmakers to vote on the legislation that’s emerged as a focal point to his leftist administration.
title: Chile’s Government Sets Pension Reform Bill on Fast Track

description: Rivals for centuries, China and Russia now have a de facto alliance, even if it’s failed to reach the high, “no limits” bar that Presidents Xi Jinping and Vladimir Putin set just weeks before Russia’s invasion of Ukraine in February 2022. The economic, military and political ties nurtured over the past decade between the world’s two most powerful authoritarian states — both of which aim to upend at least parts of the US-dominated, post-Cold War order — have grown as a result of the war, despite
title: Why Are Xi and Putin ‘Best Friends’?

description: President Joe Biden’s top economic adviser on Thursday will present a forceful defense of the administration’s new tariffs on Chinese imports, saying the measures are necessary to avoid more economic turbulence from unfair trade practices that threaten to undo recent manufacturing and job gains.
title: Brainard Says Tariffs Needed to Avoid New ‘China Shock’ in US

description: Michael Cohen Photographer: David Dee Delgado/Getty Images
title: Michael Cohen Back on the Stand at Trump Hush-Money Trial

description: Germany’s federal government expects to collect a combined €41.6 billion ($45.2 billion) less in tax revenue through 2028 than estimated in October, potentially complicating already testy negotiations over next year’s budget.
title: Germany Expects €42 Billion Less in Tax Revenue Through 2028

description: South African President Cyril Ramaphosa visited the site of a collapsed building on Thursday and gave assurances that no effort would be spared to extract the victims who remained trapped beneath the rubble.
title: Ramaphosa Pledges to Extract Victims From Collapsed Building

description: President Joe Biden has exerted executive privilege over recordings from the investigation into his handling of classified documents, escalating a fight with congressional Republicans as they plan a vote Thursday to hold Attorney General Merrick Garland in contempt of Congress.
title: Biden Refuses to Give House Tapes of Hur Interview on Documents

description: Prime Minister Rishi Sunak said he would stay on as a member of Parliament even if his ruling Conservative Party loses the UK general election expected later this year — the first time he’s publicly commented on his future career plans were the Tories to be defeated.
title: Sunak Says He’d Stay as MP Even If His Tories Lose UK Election

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s two war-cabinet partners are openly challenging his indecision over postwar Gaza — even siding with the US in pushing for Palestinian rule of the devastated coastal strip.
title: Israel’s War-Cabinet Rift Bursts Into Open Over Postwar Gaza

description: Get caught up on the day’s political news
title: Pledges Polished: Labour Makes Its Pre-Election Pitch

description: Each day, Bloomberg journalists take you across a selection of towns and cities as they gear up for the big vote.
title: India’s Financial Capital Suffers Political Apathy: India Votes

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy met with key commanders in the northeastern city of Kharkiv as his military fights to prevent Kremlin troops from occupying new territory in the region.
title: Zelenskiy Gathers Commanders in Kharkiv Amid Russian Offensive

description: A legal battle over South Africa’s newly enacted national health-insurance law is brewing and is likely to end up in the nation’s top court.
title: South Africa Gears Up for Legal Battle Over Health-Care Revamp

description: Support for the main Irish opposition party Sinn Fein is declining, according to an Irish Times poll, a change for the party that has been on course to oust the incumbent government.
title: Sinn Fein’s Support Falls Again, Irish Times Poll Signals

description: Benin’s government agreed to unblock oil exports from neighboring Niger after officials from China National Petroleum Corp. intervened in a dispute between the two countries.
title: Benin Unblocks Niger Oil Shipments After Chinese Intervention

description: Welcome to Balance of Power, bringing you the latest in global politics. If you haven’t yet, sign up here.
title: The Bitter Fruit of Europe’s Hardening Political Divides

description: Shortly after Israel’s United Nations envoy began speaking to the Security Council last month about a membership bid for Palestinians, the world body’s webcast of the historic session went dark.
title: UN Cuts Back on Hiring and Air Conditioning Over Tight Budget

description: Cannabis advocacy groups in Thailand urged the government to reconsider a plan to relist marijuana as a narcotic to protect the interest of a nascent industry and a large community of weed growers.
title: Thai Cannabis Groups Rally Against Plan to Relist Plant as Drug

description: Hezbollah said it launched “more than 60 rockets” at Israeli military sites on Thursday in response to an attack that killed one of its senior commanders.
title: Hezbollah Fires Missile Barrage at Israel After Commander Death

description: A South Korean court rejected a request brought by doctors to suspend a government plan to increase the number of medical school seats, which sparked a walkout by physicians that has strained the health care system.
title: Court Rejects South Korean Doctors’ Request on Med School Quota

description: German authorities said they’ve launched an investigation into a member of the lower house of parliament for the far-right Alternative for Germany party suspected of corruption and money laundering.
title: Germany Probing Far-Right Lawmaker for Alleged Corruption

description: The Biden administration is initiating a suite of policies that it says will help foster a deeper domestic supply chain for solar panels, following pleas from US manufacturers confronting a surge of tariff-free imports.
title: Biden Seeks to Bolster Solar Manufacturers With Tax and Trade Moves

description: Thailand’s new Finance Minister Pichai Chunhavajira urged the central bank to improve access to credit for retail borrowers and small business, while reiterating the need to synchronize fiscal and monetary policies to support Southeast Asia’s second-largest economy.
title: Thai Finance Chief Bats for Loan Access in Absence of Rate Cut

description: Chancellor of the Exchequer Jeremy Hunt will meet business executives at his grace-and-favor residence in leafy Buckinghamshire on Thursday as he tries to secure more company listings in the UK.
title: UK’s Hunt Gathers Executives to Pitch for More London Listings

description: Dutch coalition parties seeking to form a government six months after an election say they plan to significantly reduce migration and undo environmental measures, in a rightward shift that may draw the ire of the Netherlands’ largest companies as well as the European Union.
title: New Dutch Government to Crack Down on Migration, Green Measures

description: Slovak Prime Minister Robert Fico was being treated in intensive care in a “very serious” but stable condition a day after he was shot in what the government called a politically motivated assassination attempt.
title: Slovak Leader in Intensive Care After Assassination Attempt

description: The ECB is stepping up pressure on lenders to speed their exit from the country.
title: Europe’s Banks Find Breaking Up With Russia Is Hard to Do

description: UK plans to compensate thousands of victims of a decades-old contaminated blood scandal risk undermining Prime Minister Rishi Sunak’s ability to deliver a tax-cutting pre-election budget in the autumn.
title: Infected Blood Payouts Threaten Rishi Sunak’s Pre-Election Plan for Further Tax Cuts

description: Russia, a top global supplier of diesel, has been slashing its exports of the fuel in recent months, leading to widespread speculation that Ukrainian drone attacks are cutting how much the nation’s refineries can make.
title: The Real Reason Behind Russian Diesel Export Slump This Year

description: Two House committees on Thursday will consider whether to recommend that US Attorney General Merrick Garland be held in contempt of Congress.
title: Garland Faces Contempt Votes in Congressional Subpoena Standoff

description: India’s election is past the halfway mark, with campaigning between the main political parties heating up just like the soaring temperatures across the country.
title: The Key Constituencies to Watch in India’s High-Stakes Election

description: Thousands of unionized graduate student workers at University of California campuses across the state are poised to walk off the job after members voted to authorize leadership to call a strike, escalating tensions stemming from the university’s response to pro-Palestinian protests on campus.
title: University of California Students OK Strike Over Campus Protest
